text: Generally I use it to write code :thinking_face:
I wonder what's the advantage of writing test only in Kotlin?

<@U0ESBF4AV> , some thoughts.

1) You do not need to ship all the Kotlin methods with the Production app
2) You do not need to compromise your main app. If for whatever reason your organisation decides to stop using Kotlin, app and tests are separated.

attachments.fallback: [December 19th, 2016 12:09 AM] nikoyuwono: I wonder what's the advantage of writing test only in Kotlin?
attachments.text: I wonder what's the advantage of writing test only in Kotlin?

text: I have always found is a good mechanism to introduce Kotlin awareness in an organisation. Start using Kotlin in your tests and involving developers. After a period to evaluate whether everybody feels good with it, you can decide to introduce it in the application.
